  "prompt": "Is Ravana's golden lanka still in Sri Lanka?",
  "response": "The existence of Ravana's golden Lanka, as described in the ancient Indian epic Ramayana, is a matter of mythology and legend rather than historical fact. In the Ramayana, Lanka is portrayed as a magnificent kingdom ruled by the demon king Ravana. \n\nWhile Sri Lanka is often associated with the mythological Lanka, there is no archaeological evidence to suggest that a city or kingdom matching the description of Ravana's golden Lanka ever existed in Sri Lanka. The story of Ravana's golden Lanka is part of Hindu mythology and not considered a factual historical account. \n\nModern Sri Lanka is a country with a rich history and culture, but the tales of golden Lanka remain part of its mythological heritage rather than its documented history.",
